    <section id="overview" class="section">
      <h2>1. Overview</h2>
      <p>
        Vehicle Tips LLC creates educational and promotional automotive content across platforms including 
        <strong>YouTube</strong> and <strong>Amazon Influencer</strong>. These policies explain how we handle filming, bookings, usage rights, 
        and talent fees related to digital content. Service policies for mechanical work remain on the 
        <a href="policies.html">Warranty & Policies</a> page.
      </p>
      <a class="backtop" href="#top">↑ Back to top</a>
    </section>

    <section id="youtube" class="section">
      <h2>2. YouTube Policy</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Educational Focus:</strong> Content prioritizes repair tips, diagnostics, and product/tool education.</li>
        <li><strong Editorial Control:</strong> Publishing decisions, titles, edits, and thumbnails are at our sole discretion.</li>
        <li><strong>Scheduling:</strong> Filming during service is optional and only with consent (see Privacy & Filming Consent).</li>
        <li><strong>Brand Features:</strong> Sponsored segments or product features must be pre-approved when applicable.</li>
      </ul>
      <a class="backtop" href="#top">↑ Back to top</a>
    </section>

    <section id="amazon" class="section">
      <h2>3. Amazon Influencer Policy</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Product Coverage:</strong> Tools, parts, and accessories may be reviewed or demonstrated.</li>
        <li><strong>Affiliate Links:</strong> When links are used, appropriate disclosures are included (see Sponsorship & Disclosures).</li>
        <li><strong>Brand Coordination:</strong> For vendor requests, please provide product info, sample availability, and timelines.</li>
      </ul>
      <a class="backtop" href="#top">↑ Back to top</a>
    </section>

    <section id="booking" class="section">
      <h2>4. Content Booking</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Separate from Service:</strong> Content creation is booked separately from mechanic work to avoid impacting service quality or timing.</li>
        <li><strong>Lead Time:</strong> Please request content bookings in advance with target dates and goals.</li>
        <li><strong>Scope Agreement:</strong> We’ll confirm the format (e.g., long-form video, short, photos, livestream) and approximate runtime.</li>
      </ul>
      <a class="backtop" href="#top">↑ Back to top</a>
    </section>

    <section id="fees" class="section">
      <h2>5. Talent Fees</h2>
      <p>
        Talent/creator fees apply for on-camera work, narration, brand integrations, live features, and editorial content produced on request. 
        Rates vary by scope and usage. <strong>For a custom quote, please email</strong> 
        <a href="mailto:vehicletips757@gmail.com">vehicletips757@gmail.com</a>.
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Factors:</strong> complexity, shooting time, travel, editing, deadlines, and usage rights.</li>
        <li><strong>Deposits:</strong> Content bookings typically require a deposit to hold the date.</li>
      </ul>
      <a class="backtop" href="#top">↑ Back to top</a>
    </section>

    <section id="deliverables" class="section">
      <h2>6. Deliverables</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Define in Writing:</strong> We confirm deliverables before filming (e.g., 1× YouTube video, 1× short, 3× photos).</li>
        <li><strong>Edits:</strong> Up to 1–2 minor edit rounds may be included unless otherwise agreed.</li>
        <li><strong>Reshoots:</strong> Substantial changes or reshoots may be billed separately.</li>
      </ul>
      <a class="backtop" href="#top">↑ Back to top</a>
    </section>

    <section id="usage" class="section">
      <h2>7. Usage & Licensing</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Channels:</strong> By default, content is published on Vehicle Tips LLC channels.</li>
        <li><strong>Client Usage:</strong> If a client/brand wants to use finished content on their channels, website, or ads, a separate usage license is required.</li>
        <li><strong>License Terms:</strong> License scope (duration, platforms, regions, ad vs. organic) will be specified in the quote.</li>
        <li><strong>Rights Granted to Us:</strong> With consent to film, you grant Vehicle Tips LLC a worldwide, non-exclusive, perpetual, royalty-free license to use the footage for educational, promotional, and commercial purposes.</li>
      </ul>
      <a class="backtop" href="#top">↑ Back to top</a>
    </section>

    <section id="disclosure" class="section">
      <h2>8. Sponsorship & Disclosures</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>FTC Compliance:</strong> Sponsored content and affiliate links will be clearly disclosed.</li>
        <li><strong>Opinions:</strong> Reviews and opinions are our own unless otherwise stated.</li>
      </ul>
      <a class="backtop" href="#top">↑ Back to top</a>
    </section>

    <section id="privacy" class="section">
      <h2>9. Privacy & Filming Consent</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Consent Required:</strong> We do not record identifying features (faces, addresses, license plates) without clear permission.</li>
        <li><strong>Anonymized Shots:</strong> We may capture close-ups of parts, tools, or general steps that don’t reveal personal information.</li>
        <li><strong>No Impact on Service:</strong> If extra time is needed specifically for filming, a content booking will be scheduled separately.</li>
        <li><strong>No Obligation:</strong> You may opt out of any recording before work begins.</li>
      </ul>
      <a class="backtop" href="#top">↑ Back to top</a>
    </section>

    <section id="cancellation" class="section">
      <h2>10. Cancellations & Rescheduling</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Notice:</strong> Please provide notice as early as possible if you need to change dates.</li>
        <li><strong>Within 72 Hours:</strong> Late cancellations for content bookings may be non-refundable due to reserved time and prep.</li>
        <li><strong>Weather/Safety:</strong> Weather or safety concerns may require rescheduling at no penalty.</li>
      </ul>
      <a class="backtop" href="#top">↑ Back to top</a>
    </section>

    <section id="payments" class="section">
      <h2>11. Payments</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Invoices:</strong> Payment method and schedule are provided with your booking confirmation.</li>
        <li><strong>Deposits:</strong> Deposits may be required to secure dates and begin pre-production.</li>
        <li><strong>Separate from Service:</strong> Content fees are separate from mechanic labor rates and invoices.</li>
      </ul>
      <a class="backtop" href="#top">↑ Back to top</a>
    </section>

    <section id="contact" class="section">
